# Task ID could be an issue id/number from JIRA or GitHub, etc.
#
# Type can be
#   feat     (new feature)
#   fix      (bug fix)
#   refactor (improve code without new functionality)
#   style    (white spaces, formatting, linting fixes, etc.)
#   docs     (changes to documentation)
#   test     (adding or refactoring tests)
#   ci       (changes to CI configurations and scripts)
#   chore    (dependency updates and misc maintenance changes)
#   wip      (work in progress commit -- these should be squashed before merging)
#
# Include ! after the type to indicate a breaking change